The paper deals with path planning for an unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) with remote sensing capabilities, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The problem is formulated as a dynamically-constrained traveling salesman problem with neighborhoods, which involves optimization and control, making categories such as systems and control (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG) likely candidates. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of numerical simulations, which suggests the possibility of computer vision (cs.CV) being relevant.
